Description: Ostracon, limestone: on one side only, eight lines of a painted administrative text recording amounts of work done.
Curator's comments: For a related text see O. Berlin P 11292 ('Hieratische Papyrus aus den Königlichen Museen zu Berlin III’ [Leipzig 1911], pls 30—30a); cf. also W.K. Simpson, ‘Inscribed Material from the Pennsylvania-Yale Excavations at Abydos’ (New Haven and Philadelphia 1995), pp. 16-24). Bibliography: K.Kitchen, 'Ramesside Inscriptions' I (Oxford, 1975), 127-8; 'idem', 'Ramesside Inscriptions, Translated and Annotated: Notes and Comments' I (Oxford, 1993), p.105; H.Frankfort e.a., 'The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos' (London, 1933), I, p.94 and II, pls 90-91(ostracon no.1).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393830) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393830)
